{"by":"bitwize","id":47780041,"parent":47776667,"text":"I remember some of the malarkey done with the X11 SHAPE extension. There was a program called xmascot. You could give it an xpm of a character or use one of the presets—typically a cute animal or some sort or a chibi anime waifu. It would show a dangling figurine of this character right on your desktop, autogenerating a few frames of rotation so it could swing from side to side.<p>Of course X11 is four olds, and there&#x27;s probably some security justification for not having nonrectangular windows in Wayland, and&#x2F;or &quot;that&#x27;s a compositor implementation detail and outside the scope of the Wayland protocol&quot;.","time":1776265173,"type":"comment"}